originalText.text: I am so glad I found Mollie's practice. Her approach to working in session is not only professional and courteous but deeply empathetic and relaxed. She is an incredible listener, to the point that from very early on working together I felt as though I was talking to an old friend, or a cousin you'd go to for advice. Her ability to not only distill important clinical takeaways but make them applicable in the present tense is also commendable. I highly recommend reaching out to Mollie's practice for a consultation if you are looking for an amazing therapist

originalText.text: As someone who has been a clinician and a business consultant, working with relationships for over two decades, I can honestly say Mollie is one of the best in the industry. She is professional, intelligent, intuitive, and has an innate ability to understand the dynamics of an interaction. She gets to the heart of the matter quickly, teaches practical tools, and brings compassion while helping her clients create meaningful connections and more productive interactions. If you seek to work with a qualified, lovely, and talented therapist, look no further than Mollie Eliasof.

originalText.text: So grateful to Mollie for many reasons. Aside from the fact that she can geek out with me in dance references and metaphors, she’s got an infectious air of playfulness that I, personally, find so comforting. She’s generous, supportive, and an unwavering advocate of celebrating all the little victories. I trust Mollie and believe she’s given me a lot of sound, practical tools to use as well as consistently helped me realize what I already possessed. She’ll also give you that nudge when you’re (mostly) ready for a challenge.

originalText.text: Mollie is an amazing clinician & human being. I trust her clinical instincts and ability to treat any patient that I may send her way. She is always responsive, and kind and above all makes therapy a place to drawn insights & grow for anyone she works with.

originalText.text: Mollie is an excellent and knowledgeable therapist with extensive training in Gottman Method couples therapy. She's passionate about helping people navigate personal and relationship challenges and improve overall quality of life. Mollie is very insightful, warm, caring and an empathic listener.
